  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e22" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Procedure for employee resignations</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>Subject to the terms of a collective agreement or specific regulation made under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96385_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Public Service Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, the procedure respecting employee resignations shall be</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e36">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>an employee wishing to resign should submit a resignation in writing to the employing ministry through normal channels and is expected to give 30Â days notice of resignation, or</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e45">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>where an employee does not submit a written resignation but is absent without leave for 3 days immediately following an oral resignation, the employee shall be deemed to have resigned on the date of the employee's oral resignation.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 64/2021, s. 6.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions of the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96385_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Public Service Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 385, s. 25.]</reg:provisionsnote>
